statement:
Event streaming APIs with Server-Sent Events enable real-time data push to clients using standard HTTP. SSE advantages over WebSockets: uses standard HTTP (no protocol upgrade); works through HTTP/2 multiplexing; automatic reconnection built into browser EventSource API; simpler server implementation (just write to response stream); load balancers handle SSE connections natively (no special WebSocket proxy configuration). Implementation: server sends text/event-stream content type; each event is a data: {json}

 block; optional id field enables client to resume from last event ID on reconnection; server sends heartbeat comments (:heartbeat

) to keep connection alive through idle timeouts. Client: const source = new EventSource('/api/events'); source.onmessage = handler; source handles reconnection automatically. Use cases: live dashboard updates, notification delivery, real-time progress tracking, live feed updates.
